> <OLD>
>
> That was the beauty of it all.  Thanks tot he huge raging energon and
> explosive fueled fire that the trio were left with, even enhanced senses
> would be of no use now over against the raging brush fire about the jungle.
> At least, that was BLACKARACHNIA'S thought in it as she used her beast mode
> to head away along the trees, hopefully obscured against the darkness while
> she let her autorepair system work over on her damaged cloak system.

<NEW>

KILLER PUNCH sagged against a tree for a moment his energies on a low
ebb. It would be obvious only now that his last stance against
BLACKARACHNIA was a bluff. Had she pushed it he definitely would have
folded.

Looking down at BAZOOKA and GUILE DART he kicked at them as they were
slowly coming around as their reserves kicked in. "Stupid insects set
off a fire!" KILLER PUNCH said. "We've got to go. Now!"

GUILE DART climbed slowly to his feet as BAZOOKA tried to do much the same.

"Where to?" BAZOOKA said. "Magmatron is insane with power now and
Saberback is the one pushing the buttons."

Looking around for a moment GUILE DART shrugged. "I don't know, but we
can't stay here in the fire."

The trio began to trudge away, opposite the direction that BLACKARACHNIA took.

(TAG)

- Preston
